First, you need to compile your document. For this, you can use the `pdflatex` command in the terminal or command prompt. 

After the document is compiled, you'll get a.pdf file with the table of contents at the beginning.

However, if you want to generate the table of contents manually, you can use the following commands:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\chapter{Introduction}
\chapter* {Methodology}
\chapter{Results}
\chapter{Discussion}
\chapter{Conclusion}
\chapter{References}

\section{1.1 Introduction}
\section{1.2 Objectives}

