```

In this example, `\tableofcontents` command generates the table of contents. Each `\chapter` and `\section` command represents a new chapter or section, respectively. 

The `\chapter*` command is used for a chapter with no numbering. If you don't use this command, the chapter will be numbered in the table of contents, but it will also appear in the main text.

The `\section` command with the asterisk (`\section*{...}`) generates a section with no numbering in the table of contents. This is useful for subtitles or subsections that you don't want to appear in the table of contents.

After compiling the document, you'll get a.pdf file with the table of contents at the beginning, showing all the chapters and sections you've defined.

